-SystemsManager:-
  -RunCommand
    -ssm agent will be by default in amazon linux and ubuntu,
    -windows,whereas in other it should be installed
    -can be used to update softwares or add users without loggin in
    -can use shell script and do your task to many no of servers

  -ParameterStore
    -used to store parameters like secure(username,data) and insecure data(instance type)
    -we can use this parameters in cloud formation instead of usign real username and password
    -in parameter name shouldnt start with aws(correct eg:/b2aws)
    -in parameters passwords cant be auto generated and no cross account access

  -HybridActivations & Fleet Manager:
    -used to manage instancs on other clouds or on on-premises data center
    -create a activation 

  -patch manager:
    -used to do patching using systems manager 

  -Automations with Documents:
    -automating with the documents they give

  -ControlTower:
    -helps us managing for creating a high level architecture for beginner(creates separate OU's for log servers,patching servers, audits,.etc) 

